#: ../../topic_folders/hosts_instructors/hosts_instructors_checklist.md:98
msgid "Rule #1: Be kind"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/hosts_instructors/hosts_instructors_checklist.md:100
msgid "This means to be inclusive, respectful, mindful and welcoming."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/hosts_instructors/hosts_instructors_checklist.md:102
msgid "Rule #2: Remember that we are all learners"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/hosts_instructors/hosts_instructors_checklist.md:104
msgid ""
"Admitting that you don't know everything helps create a growth mindset, "
"where we are all constantly learning. When you make a mistake, calmly "
"talk about the error, how it's part of the process and necessary to make "
"progress."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/hosts_instructors/hosts_instructors_checklist.md:107
msgid "Rule #3: Be aware of demotivating attitudes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/hosts_instructors/hosts_instructors_checklist.md:109
msgid ""
"There are several things that can be demotivating or impair the learners'"
" experience. Examples of what not to do:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/hosts_instructors/hosts_instructors_checklist.md:111
msgid ""
"Take over the learner's keyboard. Instead, encourage and guide them "
"through the solution, but let them type themselves."
msgstr ""

#: ../../topic_folders/hosts_instructors/hosts_instructors_checklist.md:112
msgid ""
"Dive into deep discussions with more advanced learners (who might "
"actually not need to be there). You can have those conversations"
